BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TItem for the Syncfusion.Blazor.DropDowns.SfComboBox<TValue, TItem> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowCustom
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the component allows user defined value which does not exist in data source.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Autofill
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether suggest a first matched item in input when searching. No action happens when no matches found.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowClearButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>Specifies whether to show or hide the clear button.</para>
            <para>When the clear button is clicked, `Value`, `Text`, and `Index` properties are reset to null.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValidateOnInput
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the component validates the input or not. true, If the ValidateOnInput is enabled for form validation, then the model value will be updated on entering the value to the input. otherwise, false.The default value is false. This property is used to validate the form on typing into the input and updating the model value. The ValueChange event will be fired after the component lost its focus.

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the id of the DropDownList component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the content that has to be passed.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expression for defining the value of the bound.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowFiltering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>When AllowFiltering is set to true, show the filter bar (search box) of the component.</para>
            <para>The filter action retrieves matched items through the `Filtering` event based on the characters typed in the search TextBox.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS class name that can be appended with the root element of the DropDownList. One or more custom CSS classes can be added to a DropDownList.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FilterBarPlaceholder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the value to be displayed as a watermark text on the filter bar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FloatLabelType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the floating label behavior of the DropDownList that the placeholder text floats above the DropDownList based on the following values.
            <para>Possible values are:</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Never</term>
            <description>Never floats the label in the DropDownList when the placeholder is available.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Always</term>
            <description>The floating label always floats above the DropDownList.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Auto</term>
            <description>The floating label floats above the DropDownList after focusing it or when enters the value in it.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FooterTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to the footer container of the popup list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to the header container of the popup list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as styles, class, and more to the root element.
            If you configured both property and equivalent html attributes, then the component considers the property value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            <para>If you configured both the property and equivalent input attribute, then the component considers the property value.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Index
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the index of the selected item in the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IndexChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the index changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placeholder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text that is shown as a hint or placeholder until the user focuses or enter a value in DropDownList. The property is depending on the FloatLabelType property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PopupHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the popup list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PopupWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the popup list. By default, the popup width sets based on the width of
            the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Readonly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the boolean value whether the DropDownList allows the user to change the value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableVirtualization
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Virtual Scrolling feature is used to display a large amount of data that you require without buffering the entire load of a huge database records in the DropDowns, that is, when scrolling, the datamanager request is sent to fetch some amount of data from the server dynamically.
            To achieve this scenario with DropDowns, set the EnableVirtualization to true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemsCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The data can be fetched in popup based on ItemsCount, when enabled the EnableVirtualization.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the value of the selected item in the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the value changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to the selected list item in the input element of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>Specifies the width of the component. By default, the component width sets based on the width of
            its parent container.</para>
            <para>You can also set the width in pixel values.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the tab order of the DropDownList component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content of input has changed and gets focus-out.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnInput
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers each time when the value of input has changed.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnBlur
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the input loses the focus.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the input gets focus.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>Enable or disable persisting component's state between page reloads.</para>
            <para>If enabled,  the `Value` state will be persisted.</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Value</term>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to each list item present in the popup.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GroupTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to the group headers present in the popup list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NoRecordsTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template design and assigns it to popup list of component, when no data is available on the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ActionFailureTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the template and assigns it to the popup list content of the component, when the data fetch request from the remote server fails.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortOrder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>Specifies the `SortOrder` to sort the data source.</para>
            <para>The available type of sort orders are.</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>None</term>
            <description>The data source is not sorting.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Ascending</term>
            <description>The data source is sorting with ascending order.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Descending</term>
            <description>The data source is sorting with descending order.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the component allows the user to interact with it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataSource
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>Accepts the list items either through local or remote service and binds it to the component.</para>
            <para>It can be an array of JSON Objects or an instance of `DataManager`.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Query
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accepts the external `Query` that execute along with data processing.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FilterType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Determines on which filter type, the component needs to be considered on search action.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IgnoreCase
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>When set to `false`, consider the `case-sensitive` on performing the search to find suggestions.</para>
            <para>By default, consider the casing.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IgnoreAccent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            ignoreAccent set to true, then ignores the diacritic characters or accents when filtering.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            specifies the z-index value of the component popup element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

BoundAttributes.Name: FloatLabelType

<summary>
            Specifies the floating label behavior of the DropDownList that the placeholder text floats above the DropDownList based on the following values.
            <para>Possible values are:</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Never</term>
            <description>Never floats the label in the DropDownList when the placeholder is available.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Always</term>
            <description>The floating label always floats above the DropDownList.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Auto</term>
            <description>The floating label floats above the DropDownList after focusing it or when enters the value in it.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the of the active breadcrumb item. This property contains Url string of active breadcrumb item. This property is updated only when the has value. @code { private string activeItem = "https://blazor.syncfusion.com/demos/menu-bar/default-functionalities"; } ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the maximum number of breadcrumb items to be visible in the breadcrumb component.
            If the number of items exceeds this count, then items are rendered based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.OverflowMode" /> property. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            The number of breadcrumb items to be visible in breadcrumb component. The default value is <c>0</c>. 
            </value>
            <remarks>
            The <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.MaxItems" /> is applicable only if the number of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbItem" /> is greater than <c>2</c>.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates how to display breadcrumb items when the breadcrumb items count exceeds <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.MaxItems" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbOverflowMode" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbOverflowMode.Menu" />
            </value>
            <remarks>
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Hidden</c>, the exceeded items will be hidden and while clicking on the previous item, the hidden item will become visible.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Collapsed</c>,  only the first and last items will be visible, and the remaining items will be hidden with collapsed icon.
            When the collapsed icon is clicked, all items become visible and scroll will be enabled if the space is not enough to show all items. 
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Menu</c>, it shows the number of breadcrumb items that can be accommodated within the container space, and creates a sub menu with the remaining items.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Wrap</c>, it wraps the items on multiple lines when the Breadcrumbs width exceeds the container space.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Scroll</c>, it shows an HTML scroll bar when the Breadcrumbs width exceeds the container space.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>None</c>, it shows all the items on a single line.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the built-in item navigation is enabled or not. The breadcrumb component navigates to url based on the item clicked by user. true, if built-in item navigation is enabled; otherwise, false.The default value is true. You can handle navigation in using event by setting as false.

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableActiveItemNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the navigation is enabled for active item (last breadcrumb item). true, if the navigation is enabled for last breadcrumb item and it is clickable. otherwise, false.The default value is false.

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to persist component's state between page reloads. When set to <c>true</c>, the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.ActiveItem" /> property is persisted.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the component's state persistence is enabled. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            Component's <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.ActiveItem" /> property will be stored in browser local storage to persist component's state when page reloads.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl

<summary>
            Gets or sets whether the right to left direction is enabled for breadcrumb component.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the right to left direction is enabled for breadcrumb component. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>

            <summary>
            Partial Class SfSidebar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The SfSidebar component is an expandable and collapsible component that typically acts as a side container to place primary or secondary content alongside the main content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Changed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the state(expand/collapse) of the component is changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClose
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is ready to close.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is created.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Destroyed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component gets destroyed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is ready to open.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the sidebar element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the child content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the animation transitions on expanding or collapsing the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseOnDocumentClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Sidebar needs to be closed or not when the document area is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DockSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the size of the Sidebar in dock state. Dock size can be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the docking state of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableGestures
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables the expand or collapse while swiping in the touch devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the persisting component's state between page reloads. If enabled, isOpen state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Sidebar in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the Sidebar component is open or close.
            When the Sidebar type is set to `Auto`,
            the component will be expanded in the desktop and collapsed in the mobile mode regardless of the isOpen property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpenChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MediaQuery
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the media query string for resolution, when opens the Sidebar.
            Example: assigning media query value to '(min-width: 600px)' will open the sidebar component only when the provided resolution is met else the sidebar will be in closed state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowBackdrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to apply overlay options to the main content or not when the Sidebar is in an open state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows to place the sidebar inside the target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expanding types of the Sidebar.
            `Over` - The sidebar floats over the main content area.
            `Push` - The sidebar pushes the main content area to appear side-by-side and shrinks the main content within the screen width.
            `Slide` - The sidebar translates the x and y positions of the main content area based on the sidebar width.
            The main content area will not be adjusted within the screen width.
             `Auto` - Sidebar with `Over` type in mobile resolution and `Push` type in other higher resolutions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Sidebar. By default, the width of the Sidebar sets based on the size of its content.
            Width can also be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-index of the Sidebar. It is applicable only when sidebar act as the overlay type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the animation transitions on expanding or collapsing the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseOnDocumentClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Sidebar needs to be closed or not when the document area is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DockSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the size of the Sidebar in dock state. Dock size can be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the docking state of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableGestures
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables the expand or collapse while swiping in the touch devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the persisting component's state between page reloads. If enabled, isOpen state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Sidebar in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the Sidebar component is open or close.
            When the Sidebar type is set to `Auto`,
            the component will be expanded in the desktop and collapsed in the mobile mode regardless of the isOpen property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpenChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MediaQuery
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the media query string for resolution, when opens the Sidebar.
            Example: assigning media query value to '(min-width: 600px)' will open the sidebar component only when the provided resolution is met else the sidebar will be in closed state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowBackdrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to apply overlay options to the main content or not when the Sidebar is in an open state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows to place the sidebar inside the target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expanding types of the Sidebar.
            `Over` - The sidebar floats over the main content area.
            `Push` - The sidebar pushes the main content area to appear side-by-side and shrinks the main content within the screen width.
            `Slide` - The sidebar translates the x and y positions of the main content area based on the sidebar width.
            The main content area will not be adjusted within the screen width.
             `Auto` - Sidebar with `Over` type in mobile resolution and `Push` type in other higher resolutions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Sidebar. By default, the width of the Sidebar sets based on the size of its content.
            Width can also be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-index of the Sidebar. It is applicable only when sidebar act as the overlay type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTab
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>

            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets ID attribute for the tab element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Child Content for Tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation settings of the Tabs component. The animation effect can be applied to activate the tab with duration and delay.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the CSS classes to the root element of the Tabs that helps to customize the component styles.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting component's state between page reloads.
            If enabled, the tabs selected item will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowDragAndDrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the Tab allows drag and drop over tab items. Tab item has been reordered based on the dropped item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DragArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the area in which the draggable element movement will be occurring. Outside that area will be restricted
            for the draggable element movement. By default, the draggable element movement occurs with Tabitems.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in the right to left (RTL) direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the orientation of the Tab header.
            The possible values are:
            - Top: Places the Tab header on the top.
            - Bottom: Places the Tab header at the bottom.
            - Left: Places the Tab header at the left.
            - Right: Places the Tab header at the right.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the Tabs component. By default, Tab height is set based on the height of its parent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A list of items that are used to configure the Tabs component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the modes for the Tab content.
            The possible modes are:
            `Dynamic` Load the Tab content dynamically, which is rendering its content when switching its header.
            `Init` Loads all the tab contents on initial loading.
            `Demand` Loads the Tab content when required but keeps the content once it is rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Locale
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Overrides the global culture and localization value for this component. Default global culture is 'en-US'.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the display mode which will be applied when the Tabs exceeds the viewing area.
            The possible modes are:
            - Scrollable: All the elements will be displayed in a single line with horizontal scrolling enabled.
            - Popup: Tab container will hold the items that can be placed within the available space and the rest of the items will be moved to the popup.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollStep
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the scrolling distance that applies when scrolling in Tab and enabled Scrollable mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the index for activating the Tab item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCloseButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether to show the close button in the Tab header or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReorderActiveTab
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to re-order tab items to show active tab item in the header area or popup when OverflowMode is Popup.
            </summary>
            <value>
            true, if active tab item should be visible in header area instead of pop-up; otherwise, false. The default value is true.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTab.ReorderActiveTab" /> Property is only applicable when OverflowMode is popup.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Tabs component. By default, Tab width sets based on the width of its parent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as id, title etc., to the tab element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options for positioning the icon in the Tab item header. This property depends on the `IconCss` property.
            The possible values are:
            - left: Places the icon to the `left` of the item.
            - top: Places the icon on the `top` of the item.
            - right: Places the icon to the `right` end of the item.
            - bottom: Places the icon at the `bottom` of the item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Toolbar display mode when Toolbar content exceeds the viewing area.
            Possible modes are:
            - Scrollable: All the elements are displayed in a single line with horizontal scrolling enabled.
            - Popup: Prioritized elements are displayed on the Toolbar and the rest of elements are moved to the popup.
            - MultiRow: Displays the overflow toolbar items as an in-line of a toolbar.
            - Extended: Hide the overflowing toolbar items in the next row.  Show the overflowing toolbar items when you click the expand icons.
            If the popup content overflows the height of the page, the rest of the elements will be hidden.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollStep
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the scrolling distance in scroller.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Toolbar in pixels/numbers/percentage. Number value is considered as pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as id, title etc., to the toolbar element.
            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            Child Content for Toolbar item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event triggers when click the toolbar item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Align
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the location for aligning Toolbar items on the Toolbar. Each command will be aligned according to the `Align` property.
             Possible values are:
             - Left: To align commands to the left side of the Toolbar.
             - Center: To align commands at the center of the Toolbar.
             - Right: To align commands to the right side of the Toolbar.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes (separated by space) to be used for customization of commands.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether an item should be disabled or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines htmlAttributes used to add custom attributes to Toolbar command.
            Supports HTML attributes such as style, class, etc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the unique ID to be used with button or input element of Toolbar items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Overflow
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Toolbar command display area when an element's content is too large to fit available space.
            This is applicable only to `Popup` mode. Possible values are:
            - Show:  Always shows the item as the primary priority on the Toolbar.
            - Hide: Always shows the item as the secondary priority on the popup.
            - None: No priority for display, and as per normal order moves to popup when content exceeds.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PrefixIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes separated by space used to specify an icon for the button.
            The icon will be positioned before the text content if text is available, otherwise the icon alone will be rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowAlwaysInPopup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the priority of items to display it in popup always.
            It allows to maintain toolbar item on popup always but it does not work for toolbar priority items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowTextOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies where the button text will be displayed on popup mode of the Toolbar.
            Possible values are:
            - Toolbar:  Text will be displayed on Toolbar only.
            - Overflow: Text will be displayed only when content overflows to popup.
            - Both: Text will be displayed on popup and Toolbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuffixIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes separated by space used to specify an icon for the button.
            The icon will be positioned after the text content if text is available.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the HTML element/element ID as a string that can be added as a Toolbar command.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text to be displayed on the Toolbar button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TooltipText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text to be displayed on hovering the Toolbar button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the types of command to be rendered in the Toolbar.
            Supported types are:
            - Button: Creates the Button control with its given properties like text, prefixIcon, etc.
            - Separator: Adds a horizontal line that separates the Toolbar commands.
            - Input: Creates an input element that is applicable to template rendering with Syncfusion controls like DropDownList,
            AutoComplete, etc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether an item should be hidden or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Toolbar button commands.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTreeView<TValue>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the TreeView component.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the TreeView component.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            SfTreeView component.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The TreeView component is used to represent hierarchical data in a tree like structure with advanced functions to edit, drag and drop, select with CheckBox and more.
            TreeView can be populated from a data source such as an array of data's or from DataManager.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TValue">"TValue parameter".</typeparam>

BoundAttributes.Name: TValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TValue for the Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTreeView<TValue> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary>
            Get the RenderFragment content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowDragAndDrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the TreeView allows drag and drop of nodes. To drag and drop a node in
            desktop, hold the mouse on the node, drag it to the target node and drop the node by releasing
            the mouse. For touch devices, drag and drop operation is performed by touch, touch move
            and touch end.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowEditing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables editing of the text in the TreeView node. When `AllowEditing` property is set
            to true, the TreeView allows you to edit the node by double clicking the node or by navigating to
            the node and pressing F2 key.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowMultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables multi-selection of nodes. To select multiple nodes:
             Select the nodes by holding down the CTRL key while clicking on the nodes.
             Select consecutive nodes by clicking the first node to select and hold down the SHIFT key
            and click the last node to select.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowTextWrap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables to wrap the text in the TreeView node. 
            When the `AllowTextWrap` property is set to true, the TreeView node text content will wrap to the next line
            when its text content exceeds the width of the TreeView node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of animation applied on expanding and collapsing the nodes along with duration.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoCheck
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allow us to specify the parent and child nodes to get auto check while we check or uncheck a node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CheckedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The `CheckedNodes` property is used to set the nodes that need to be checked or
            get the ID of nodes that are currently checked in the TreeView component.
            The `checkedNodes` property depends upon the value of `showCheckBox` property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CheckedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the checked nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS classes to be added with root element of the TreeView to help customize the appearance of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the TreeView component is disabled or not.
            When set to true, user interaction will not be occurred in TreeView.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the area in which the draggable element movement will be occurring. Outside that area will be restricted
            for the draggable element movement. By default, the draggable element movement occurs in the entire page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHtmlSanitizer
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines whether to allow the cross-scripting site or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables persisting TreeView state between page reloads. If enabled, following APIs will persist.
            1. `SelectedNodes` - Represents the nodes that are selected in the TreeView component.
            2. `checkedNodes`  - Represents the nodes that are checked in the TreeView component.
            3. `expandedNodes` - Represents the nodes that are expanded in the TreeView component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the action on which the node expands or collapses. The available actions are,
             `Click` - The expand/collapse operation happens when you single-click the node in both desktop and mobile devices.
             `DblClick` - The expand/collapse operation happens when you double-click the node in both desktop and mobile devices.
             `None` - The expand/collapse operation will not happen when you single-click or double-click the node in both desktop
             and mobile devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the expanded nodes in the TreeView component. We can set the nodes that need to be
            expanded or get the ID of the nodes that are currently expanded by using this property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the expanded nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Fields
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the data source and mapping fields to render TreeView nodes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FullRowNavigable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If this property is set to true, then the entire TreeView node will be navigate-able instead of text element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FullRowSelect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            On enabling this property, the entire row of the TreeView node gets selected by clicking a node.
            When disabled only the corresponding node's text gets selected.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadOnDemand
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the load on demand (Lazy load) is set to true. By disabling this property, all the tree nodes are rendered at the
            beginning itself.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the selected nodes in the TreeView component. We can set the nodes that need to be
            selected or get the ID of the nodes that are currently selected by using this property.
            On enabling `AllowMultiSelection` property we can select multiple nodes and on disabling
            it we can select only a single node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the selected nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCheckBox
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates that the nodes will display CheckBoxes in the TreeView.
            The CheckBox will be displayed next to the expand/collapse icon of the node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortOrder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the nodes are sorted in the ascending or descending order,
            or are not sorted at all. The available types of sort order are,
             `None` - The nodes are not sorted.
             `Ascending` - The nodes are sorted in the ascending order.
             `Descending` - The nodes are sorted in the ascending order.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify the HtmlAttributes for TreeView.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TreeViewTemplates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom item template of TreeView Node item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the treeview element.
            </summary>

            desktop, hold the mouse on the node, drag it to the target node and drop the node by releasing
            the mouse. For touch devices, drag and drop operation is performed by touch, touch move
            and touch end.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowEditing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables editing of the text in the TreeView node. When `AllowEditing` property is set
            to true, the TreeView allows you to edit the node by double clicking the node or by navigating to
            the node and pressing F2 key.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowMultiSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables multi-selection of nodes. To select multiple nodes:
             Select the nodes by holding down the CTRL key while clicking on the nodes.
             Select consecutive nodes by clicking the first node to select and hold down the SHIFT key
            and click the last node to select.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowTextWrap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables to wrap the text in the TreeView node. 
            When the `AllowTextWrap` property is set to true, the TreeView node text content will wrap to the next line
            when its text content exceeds the width of the TreeView node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of animation applied on expanding and collapsing the nodes along with duration.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoCheck
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allow us to specify the parent and child nodes to get auto check while we check or uncheck a node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CheckedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The `CheckedNodes` property is used to set the nodes that need to be checked or
            get the ID of nodes that are currently checked in the TreeView component.
            The `checkedNodes` property depends upon the value of `showCheckBox` property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CheckedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the checked nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS classes to be added with root element of the TreeView to help customize the appearance of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the TreeView component is disabled or not.
            When set to true, user interaction will not be occurred in TreeView.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the area in which the draggable element movement will be occurring. Outside that area will be restricted
            for the draggable element movement. By default, the draggable element movement occurs in the entire page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHtmlSanitizer
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines whether to allow the cross-scripting site or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables persisting TreeView state between page reloads. If enabled, following APIs will persist.
            1. `SelectedNodes` - Represents the nodes that are selected in the TreeView component.
            2. `checkedNodes`  - Represents the nodes that are checked in the TreeView component.
            3. `expandedNodes` - Represents the nodes that are expanded in the TreeView component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the action on which the node expands or collapses. The available actions are,
             `Click` - The expand/collapse operation happens when you single-click the node in both desktop and mobile devices.
             `DblClick` - The expand/collapse operation happens when you double-click the node in both desktop and mobile devices.
             `None` - The expand/collapse operation will not happen when you single-click or double-click the node in both desktop
             and mobile devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the expanded nodes in the TreeView component. We can set the nodes that need to be
            expanded or get the ID of the nodes that are currently expanded by using this property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ExpandedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the expanded nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Fields
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the data source and mapping fields to render TreeView nodes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FullRowNavigable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If this property is set to true, then the entire TreeView node will be navigate-able instead of text element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FullRowSelect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            On enabling this property, the entire row of the TreeView node gets selected by clicking a node.
            When disabled only the corresponding node's text gets selected.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadOnDemand
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the load on demand (Lazy load) is set to true. By disabling this property, all the tree nodes are rendered at the
            beginning itself.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedNodes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents the selected nodes in the TreeView component. We can set the nodes that need to be
            selected or get the ID of the nodes that are currently selected by using this property.
            On enabling `AllowMultiSelection` property we can select multiple nodes and on disabling
            it we can select only a single node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedNodesChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the selected nodes changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCheckBox
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates that the nodes will display CheckBoxes in the TreeView.
            The CheckBox will be displayed next to the expand/collapse icon of the node.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortOrder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the nodes are sorted in the ascending or descending order,
            or are not sorted at all. The available types of sort order are,
             `None` - The nodes are not sorted.
             `Ascending` - The nodes are sorted in the ascending order.
             `Descending` - The nodes are sorted in the ascending order.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specify the HtmlAttributes for TreeView.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TreeViewTemplates
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom item template of TreeView Node item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the treeview element.
            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the class/multiple classes separated by a space for the Button that is used to include an icon.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Positions the icon before or after the text content in the Button.
            The possible values are: Left: The icon will be positioned to the left of the text content.
            Right: The icon will be positioned to the right of the text content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsPrimary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows the appearance of the Button to be enhanced and visually appealing when set to `true`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsToggle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Makes the Button toggle, when set to `true`.
            When you click it, the state changes from normal to active.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of the button.
            Possible values are Button, Submit, and Reset.
            </summary>

            Specifies the duration to animate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Easing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation timing function.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Effect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation name that should be applied on while opening and closing the toast.
            If the user sets Fade animation, the toast will open with the `FadeIn` effect and close with the `FadeOut` effect.
            The following are the list of animation effects available to configure to the toast:
            1. Fade
            2. FadeZoom
            3. FlipLeftDown
            4. FlipLeftUp
            5. FlipRightDown
            6. FlipRightUp
            7. FlipXDown
            8. FlipXUp
            9. FlipYLeft
            10. FlipYRight
            11. SlideBottom
            12. SlideLeft
            13. SlideRight
            14. SlideTop
            15. Zoom
            16. None.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            The possible values are:
            - Left: The icon will be positioned to the left of the text content.
            - Right: The icon will be positioned to the right of the text content.

            - Bottom: The icon will be positioned to the bottom of the text content.
            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

<summary>
            Triggers once the component rendering is completed.
            </summary>

<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the scrollable width of the PDF Viewer.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableToolbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then toolbar  of the PDF Viewer will not be visible. By default it is true and visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnnotationToolbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the edit annotation option in the toolbar will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableNavigationToolbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then left side toolbar(bookmark, thumbnail navigation toolbar) will not be visible. By default it is true and visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RetryCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the retry count for PDF Viewer service call. By default  retrycount is 1.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            This RetryCount is only applicable for Web Assembly projects alone.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableErrorDialog
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then error dialogue display in PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableCommentPanel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then text selection in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsCommentPanelOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the comment panel is in expanded or collapsed state. If it set as true, then the thumbnail panel will be expanded or open state. By default it is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableThumbnailPanel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, the thumbnail panel on the left side of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsThumbnailPanelOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the thumbnail panel is in expanded or collapsed state. If it set as true, then the thumbnail panel will be expanded or open state . By default it is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDownload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the download option in the toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePrint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the print option in the toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePrintRotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as FALSE, will suppress the page rotation of Landscape document on print action. By default it is TRUE.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PrintMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the print mode in the PDF Viewer.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsSignatureEditable
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, the signature included in the PDF Viewer will saved as ink annotation on download action in the PDF Viewer. Otherwise the signature will be flattened on downloading or saving. By default it is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableBookmarkPanel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, the bookmark panel on the left side of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHyperlink
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then hyperlink in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHandwrittenSignature
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if it is set as false, then the handwritten signature tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableInkAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the ink annotation support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RestrictZoomRequest
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, then page image will be fetched only when the zoom percentage is 100. Otherwise, mutliple page image fetched for different zoom percentages on performing zoom operation. By default it is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HyperlinkOpenState
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the URL is opened in current tab, new tab, new window . By default it is current tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then page navigation of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAutoComplete
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false,  auto complete behavior of form fields will be disabled. Be default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMagnification
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then all the zoom operations in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableShapeLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, label for shape and measure annotations can be added. It used to display the text content about the shape or measure annotation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableImportAnnotationMeasurement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disables the customization of measure values in PdfViewer.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePinchZoom
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then pinch zoom of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableZoomOptimization
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If it is set as false, then page image will be fetched for each zoom percentage values. Otherwise, page image will be fetched only when the zoom percentages are 100 %,200 %,300 %, and 400 %. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then text selection in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextSearch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then text search support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the annotation support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableFormFields
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, form fields in the PDF document can't be interacted or edited. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsFormFieldDocument
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets the value to check whether the loaded document have the form fields or not. By default it is false. If the document contains any form field it returns true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableFreeText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the free text annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextMarkupAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the textmarkup tools (highlight, strikethrough, and underline) are disabled in annotation toolbar. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableShapeAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the shape annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMeasureAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the measurement annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableStampAnnotations
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the stamp annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableStickyNotesAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the sticky notes annotation tool in the toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InteractionMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the interaction is in selection(select tool) or pan mode. By default it it selection.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsExtractText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, the PDF Viewer will extract the text from the document asynchronously after the initial loading. Once the extraction process completed  then ExtractTextCompleted event will be triggered.
            The extracted text can be accessed from event args of the ExtractTextCompleted event. By default it is false and text won't be extracted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePrint

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePrintRotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHyperlink
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHandwrittenSignature

<summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableInkAnnotation

            If it is set as false, then the ink annotation support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RestrictZoomRequest
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, then page image will be fetched only when the zoom percentage is 100. Otherwise, mutliple page image fetched for different zoom percentages on performing zoom operation. By default it is false.

BoundAttributes.Name: HyperlinkOpenState
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMagnification

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableShapeLabel

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePinchZoom

            If it is set as true, then page image will be fetched only when the zoom percentage is 100. Otherwise, mutliple page image fetched for different zoom percentages on performing zoom operation. By default it is false.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HyperlinkOpenState
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the URL is opened in current tab, new tab, new window . By default it is current tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then page navigation of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAutoComplete
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false,  auto complete behavior of form fields will be disabled. Be default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMagnification
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then all the zoom operations in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableShapeLabel
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, label for shape and measure annotations can be added. It used to display the text content about the shape or measure annotation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableImportAnnotationMeasurement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disables the customization of measure values in PdfViewer.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePinchZoom
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then pinch zoom of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableZoomOptimization
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If it is set as false, then page image will be fetched for each zoom percentage values. Otherwise, page image will be fetched only when the zoom percentages are 100 %,200 %,300 %, and 400 %. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextSelection
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then text selection in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextSearch
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then text search support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled, By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the annotation support in the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableFormFields
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, form fields in the PDF document can't be interacted or edited. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsFormFieldDocument
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets the value to check whether the loaded document have the form fields or not. By default it is false. If the document contains any form field it returns true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableFreeText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the free text annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTextMarkupAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the textmarkup tools (highlight, strikethrough, and underline) are disabled in annotation toolbar. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableShapeAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the shape annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMeasureAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the measurement annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableStampAnnotations
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the stamp annotation tool in the annotation toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableStickyNotesAnnotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as false, then the sticky notes annotation tool in the toolbar of the PDF Viewer will be disabled. By default it is true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InteractionMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the interaction is in selection(select tool) or pan mode. By default it it selection.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsExtractText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If it is set as true, the PDF Viewer will extract the text from the document asynchronously after the initial loading. Once the extraction process completed  then ExtractTextCompleted event will be triggered.
            The extracted text can be accessed from event args of the ExtractTextCompleted event. By default it is false and text won't be extracted.
            </summary>
